text: Hi! I’m taking a flight with almost a full day layover in Atlanta and was thinking to go visit the uni and the city! Something in particular to go visit? Any recommendations from the locals? :slightly_smiling_face:

elements.text: Hi! I’m taking a flight with almost a full day layover in Atlanta and was thinking to go visit the uni and the city! Something in particular to go visit? Any recommendations from the locals?

text: Piedmont Park is pretty close to campus - If you like walking you could visit Tech campus and then have a nice walk through Midtown Atlanta towards Piedmont park. There is a nice little cafe called Cafe Lucia on the way where you could stop for a coffee and a sandwhich.

text:
I'm partial to Sweet Water blue, so I upvote Sweet Water brewery. If you stop there for food, in addition to their burger, boiled peanut is a must have for visitor.
You can take MARTA/rail transportation from airport North avenue that's where the campus located. If this is your first time, I would visit the Barnes and Noble on campus as well.
